The paper deals with the problem of concept learning, which is a core topic in machine learning. The focus is on modular concept learning, where a concept is a cross product of component concepts. This is a problem that is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), and computational complexity (cs.CC). The paper discusses different types of oracle interfaces and their impact on the difficulty of learning modular concepts, which is a topic that is relevant to all of these subfields. Therefore, it is likely that the paper could be classified under any of these subcategories.
